@RedRapist  

Um, why [Stuffy Doll](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Stuffy Doll)? I'm quite aware of the countless combos with the doll, but I'm not seeing it here...? Typically, they involve focusing massive, creature-only damage all at one point (i.e. [Shivan Meteor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shivan Meteor)) but this just makes him a slightly bigger attacker...  

@occamsrazorwit  

I guess, but that requires them having a non-![Tap](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=tap&type=symbol) creature. And what if they play another, bigger creature? Or give this one trample (which ruin's stuffy doll's effectiveness)? Then you just gave them a way past your doll. I don't know. Pumping an opponent's creature with no reliable way to use it against them doesn't seem all that clever.

